lenders.name: Claire
lenders.occupational_info:
Mrs. Claire Zaglauer is an educator in language studies.  She is currently teaching English abroad in Suzhou, China. She received her MS in Education in 2009 with distinction and is currently working on her second Master’s Degree in School Leadership. Her first Master’s Degree was an award from the New York City Department of Education for educators focusing on Teaching English as a Second Language.  The cultural and linguistic diversity in New York City lends itself to an ongoing need in this area.  Ms. Zaglauer was one of few recipients for this fully funded degree program.  She accepted a position as the founding Kindergarten teacher for the first public bilingual French program in Manhattan at P.S. 84.

In 2009, Claire was issued a Bourse de Stage Pedagogique de Courte Duree in the summer of 2009 by the French Department of Education.  This was a six-week program at the University of Strasbourg for teachers involved in French and bilingualism.  During this program, Ms. Zaglauer was able to connect with French educators and University contacts in the language department which proved invaluable in the future.

With a heavy focus on language acquisition and a shift into school leadership, a position with a public bilingual French school as an administrator was a natural next step.  Claire used her contacts in bilingual education and international education to add several key programs to her new school.  These included intercultural exchange programs, internship programs and other extracurricular programs which helped to further enrich the school.

After six years in education in New York City’s urban environment, Claire Zaglauer has decided it was time for a change of scenery in order to explore international education from the foreign perspective and moved to Suzhou, China, where she is furthering her exposure to bilingual education in an immersion environment.  In addition to being an educator and learning Mandarin as a fourth language, Claire is an avid traveler and music enthusiast. She recently planned a trip to the remote Xinjiang region with her family bordering Kazakhstan and Kyrgystan with a colleague.  She regularly participates in chorale ensembles such as the Cincinnati May Festival Chorus and the New York City based Nashir! Chorus presenting Jewish and Hebrew music from around the world. Ms. Zaglauer currently resides in Suzhou, China with her husband David and their children Louisa and Liam.

lenders.name: Martin
lenders.occupational_info:
Martin is originally from Texas, though he’s lived on both the east coast and west coast of the greatest nation in the world, the United States of America. He even lived in paradise for a few years, on the beautiful island of Oahu, Hawaii. Martin spent a lot of his childhood playing baseball, soccer, basketball, and football in El Paso, Texas. If you’re unfamiliar with El Paso, listen to the Marty Robbins song of the same name, or watch the 2006 movie Glory Road, which portrays Martin’s undergraduate alma mater, University of Texas at El Paso.

Mr. Holguin graduated from UTEP in 1999 with a B.S. in Electrical Engineering. In 2006, he earned an M.S. in the same concentration from Monterey, California’s Naval Postgraduate School. Martin is currently a prospective EMBA candidate at the University of Notre Dame, where he will graduate from in May. Attending Notre Dame has been one of the greatest experiences of Martin’s life. 

Since 1999, Lt Cmdr Martin Holguin has served in the US Navy aboard five US warships in a wide variety of capacities, ranging from division officer to commanding officer. Martin also served as a Director Fellow for the Chief of Naval Operations Strategic Studies Group. Today, Mr. Holguin is on the US Third Fleet Commander’s staff as an Integrated Air and Ballistic Missile Defense Planner.

For fun and for fitness, Martin enjoys ocean swimming as well as distance running along the coast. The longest race he’s completed is a marathon, and he’s cautiously interested in running an Ultra. He likes to use the Nike+ app to track his miles, as well as his profile at DailyMile.com–he often logs somewhere between 70 and 110 miles in a month. Martin Holguin’s absolute favorite thing to do is spending time with his wife and children.
